message: Reasons the subject of this article should be unblocked in order to make the last paragraph factually correct.
Corrected "Task Force" which is current name (see organization's website, sourced. Supplied source for "1997-2002".
Verbal, instead of edit warring, please explain why you disagree.
Communications Workers of America is properly sourced and separate from the Ad-Hoc Association. CWA presently exists with a Wiki article. Ad-Hoc Association is defunct and is not as relevant.
Inconsistent. If he is homeless he is not in his house and her electronics are not destroying his health or keeping him up at night. This material is wrong and unnecessary.
"Activist" is not a proper descriptor. Cesar Chavez was a "civil rights activist", John Lennon a "peace activist". Needs a modifier or leave it out.
Vary has not sourced the word "purported". See Wikipedia's article "electromagnetic radiation and health."

Amicus briefs support lawsuits, they are not "included in" the lawsuit.
Names of organizations do not have quotation marks. Cellular Phone Task Force is a corporation incorporated in NY State.

Removed defendant's name as agreed.
